[Katamari Ball Appearance Size Modifier Player 1]
author=bungholio
description=It only makes it look bigger or smaller, uses floats so take a guess from
3f000000 and keep adding 1000000.  Set it to FFFFFFFF to make the ball
invisible while objects stick to nothing.
patch=1,EE,209889D0,extended,3F000000

[Katamari Ball Appearance Size Modifier Player 2]
author=bungholio
description=It only makes it look bigger or smaller, uses floats so take a guess from
3f000000 and keep adding 1000000.  Set it to FFFFFFFF to make the ball
invisible while objects stick to nothing.
patch=1,EE,2098C4F0,extended,3F000000

[Level Select]
author=bungholio
description=00 - Unused level?  It looks like winter.  No ground, you just fall and
warp over and over again.
01 - Make A Star 1
02 - Make A Star 2
03 - Make A Star 4
04 - Make A Star 3 (I didn&#039;t mix it up with Make A Star 4)
05 - Make A Star 5
06 - Make A Star 6
07 - Make A Star 7
08 - Make A Star 8
09 - Make A Star 9
0a - Make The Moon
0b - Make cancer
0c - Make cygnus
0d - Unknown level, access by selecting Corona Borealis or the game will
freeze while loading.
0e - Make Corona Borealis
0f - Make Pisces
10 - Make Virgo
11 - Make Ursa Major
12 - Make Gemini
13 - Make Taurus
14 - Unused, works fine if you pick a Make A Star level.
15 - Make The North Star
16 - Eternal #1 (Make A Star 4)
17 - Eternal #2 (Make A Star 8)
18 - Eternal #3 (Make The Moon)
19 - Unused level, works fine if you pick a Make A Star level.
1a - empty level where you are very small and incredibly slow, pick a
Make A Star level.
1b - almost loaded with a Make A Star level.
1c - didn&#039;t load
1d - nowhere, you just fall and warp.  game stopped after I quit
1e - same as 00?  game stopped after I quit
1f - the 2 player VS level, the game freezes after your size increases
because the king decides to interrupt but probably wasn&#039;t programmed
with something to say.

Most load in 2 player VS mode, but you&#039;ll get messed up levels that
aren&#039;t very fun.  You shouldn&#039;t pick level types that don&#039;t match the
one you select, the game likes to freeze when you do that.  By that,
I mean don&#039;t set the code to Make Ursa Major and then select a
Make A Star level, don&#039;t set Make Pisces and then go to Make Taurus
(all the constellations seemed different?).  You can select same level
types though, use Make A Star 2 with the level select code and select
any other Make A Star level (or Make The Moon) and it&#039;ll work fine,
with maybe a few graphical problems.  It&#039;s only useful for those few
unused levels that are kind of interesting.  &quot;1b&quot; and &quot;1c&quot; probably work
if you pick the right level type, I just quickly got sick of trying.


I&#039;ve got individual level record stuff too, but it&#039;s worthless.  This is for
Make A Star 1, and it&#039;s the same thing in the same order for all of them,
except I think only Make A Star levels get comets even though they
have a place in the other constellations too.
2055ffa0 ???????? - star size when viewed in constellations
2055ffa4 ???????? - comet type
2055ffa8 ???????? - the time, gives you the comet
2055ffac ???????? - the star&#039;s size
2055ffb0 ???????? - total amount of things in the star
2055ffb4 ???????? - time it took to complete reach the right size
2055ffb8 ???????? - 1st place item type amount
2055ffbc ???????? - 2nd place item type amount
2055ffc0 ???????? - 3rd place item type amount
0055ffc4 000000?? - star type
0055ffc5 000000?? - 3rd place type
0055ffc6 000000?? - 2nd place type
0055ffc7 000000?? - 1st place type
The item types go in order in the item list in the collection.  The top left
type on page 1 is &quot;00&quot;, the next 4 are &quot;01&quot;, &quot;02&quot;, &quot;03&quot;, &quot;04&quot;, then it goes
down one row starting from the left the next 5 are &quot;05&quot;, &quot;06&quot;, &quot;07&quot;, &quot;08&quot;,
&quot;09&quot;, next row down &quot;0a&quot; and repeat.  I can&#039;t remember if there were 3
or 4 rows per page.  I think there&#039;s 6 pages.
patch=1,EE,0054EA94,extended,00000000

